<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Center Center Union To Merge With National Party </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0803011894 Santiago LA TERCERA DE LA HORA in Spanish 20 
Feb 94 p 15 </F>

<F P=103> PY0803011894 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago LA TERCERA DE LA HORA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Patricia Bravo] </F>
  [Excerpt] The Center Center Union (UCC) general assembly, 
with the approval of 80 percent of those present, decided to 
merge with the National Party (PN). 
  At the end of the event, UCC President Carlos del Campo 
said: 
"We hope to materialize a new political party of national 
interest." Del Campo met with the media accompanied by PN 
President Enrique Schilling, who attended the assembly in his 
capacity as a guest. 
  The two politicians agreed on the principles that unite 
their 
respective parties, and voiced their pleasure with the request 
by a group of independent liberals headed by Luis Claro 
Lagarrigue to join the new group. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

