<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vietnamese Donation of Pencils, Notebooks Arrives </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0903004394 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 2030 GMT 
8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0903004394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A shipment of pencils and notebooks donated by 
Vietnam has arrived in Cuba. This donation, consisting of 
500,000 notebooks and the same number of pencils, arrived in the 
port of Nicaro, in the Mayari Municipality, Holguin Province. 
This donation was sent to Cuba aboard the ship (Rose Island) by 
the Vietnamese Youth League. 
  This gift from the young Vietnamese people will be 
distributed among Education Ministry schools in the provinces of 
Santiago de Cuba, Las Tunas, Granma, Guantanamo, and Holguin. 
This is the first shipment of a plan for 10 million of these 
school items. 
  The unloading at the Nicaro pier was carried out by (Rene 
Ramos Latur Nickel Mining Company) workers, with the support of 
coast guard members and students from the Mayari community. 
  Cuban Government officials and local Cuban Communist Party 
members from Mayari expressed thanks for the donation from the 
Vietnamese Youth League, and stressed the significance of this 
donation during the country's current period. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

