<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government-URGT Peace Talks Continue in Mexico </TI></H3>
<H4>   Talks End Without Agreement </H4>
<F P=102> PA0903035594 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 2044 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0903035594 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 8 Mar (NOTIMEX) -- UN Representative 
Jean Arnault said here that the Guatemalan Government and 
guerrillas today ended a new round of talks without reaching 
definite agreements, but after achieving significant headway. 
In a news conference the UN representative announced that the 
next round of talks is slated for 23-27 March in Mexico City. 
  He explained that the two topics discussed in this round 
were 
the approval of the negotiations calendar on pending topics from 
the general agenda and the topic of human rights. Arnault also 
remarked that it was not possible to complete the topics in 
these negotiations in view that by consensus all sides agreed 
that a new round of talks was necessary. 
  The government representatives and the Guatemalan National 
Revolutionary Unity (URNG) leadership had planned to complete 
talks by Monday -- talks which seek an end to the war that has 
afflicted Guatemala for more than 30 years. 

</TEXT>

