<H3> <TI>   Enthusiasm Over Brazilian Economic Plan Viewed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0803233394 </F>
<F P=103> PY0803233394 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] Buenos Aires CLARIN in Spanish on 7 
March publishes, on pages 18 and 19, a 1,200-word article about 
the "enthusiastic reaction" by the Argentine Economy Ministry to 
the Brazilian economic program and to the meeting between 
Brazilian Finance Minister Fernando Henrique Cardoso and Foreign 
Minister Celso Amorim with Argentine counterparts Guido Di Tella 
and Domingo Cavallo in Buenos Aires on 9 March. 
  The article also comments on how Argentina will profit if 
the 
Brazilian economy becomes stable and the Brazilian level of 
consumption increases. It also comments on the political 
meaning of the success of the economic program. The article 
states that Minister Cardoso will become a potential 
presidential candidate for the October elections and run against 
leftist leader Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva. 
  The article quotes the positive reactions of several current 
and former Argentine officials to the plan, stating that they 
believe "the effects of this stabilization will become visible 
in six months." It concludes by stating that conservative 
Brazilians are seeking an "anti-Lula candidate" and that if his 
plan proves successful, Fernando Henrique Cardoso will be an 
"excellent" presidential candidate. 

</TEXT>

