<H3> <TI>   DPRK Vice President Meets Congress Vice President </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0803214794 Lima EXPRESO in Spanish 24 Feb 94 p A6 </F>
<F P=103> PY0803214794 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima EXPRESO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] DPRK Vice President Kim Pyong Sik, who is the 
chairman of the North Korean Social Democratic Party's Central 
Committee, is paying an unofficial visit to Peru. He yesterday 
attended a ceremony marking the 94th anniversary of the birth of 
Dr. Luciano Castillo Colonna, the founder of the Peruvian 
Socialist Party. 
  The ceremony was attended by DPRK Ambassador to Peru Kim 
Gyong Jo, by Dr. Maria Cabredo de Castillo, and by other 
Socialist Party members. 
  The DPRK diplomat said Kim Pyong has been in Peru for some 
days to exchange views with representatives of various political 
parties, among them are the New Majority-Change 90, the Popular 
Action, and the APRA [American Popular Revolutionary Alliance]. 
  He said that during his stay in Lima, the visitor met with 
First Vice President of Congress Carlos Torres y Torres Lara. 
The DPRK vice president will leave for Ecuador and other South 
American countries. 

