<H3> <TI>   Aristide Backers Criticize CONACOM Position </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0903193494 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1700 
GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0903193494 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In Port-au-Prince, the Carrefour-Feuilles Platform 
[Plateforme de Carrefour-Feuilles] organization criticized the 
attitude of some FNCD [National Front for Change and Democracy] 
legislators who gave their support to the plan approved by the 
legislators. The Carrefour-Feuilles Platform condemns the 
decision of the CONACOM [National Congress of Democratic 
Movements] secretary general who supported the legislators' 
plan. 
  [Begin unidentified speaker recording] This plan is one way 
for the State Department, Victor Benoit, the Army, and the 
macoutes to extinguish all the hopes that the 16 December and 20 
January elections brought the Haitian people. We are 
criticizing all the FNCD legislators who let Victor Benoit and 
the State Department buy them in order to sell out the country 
so that repression and beatings replace democracy in the 
country. We call those legislators Lavalas traitors with no 
conviction. The Carrefour-Feuilles Platform is astonished to 
see that lust for power made Victor Benoit forget all the 
CONACOM militants who were killed during the coup d'etat. 
  Who is to say that they were were not accomplices in the 
killing of those militants! The State Department should either 
officially support the criminals or the return of Aristide and 
democracy to the country. Our words are our convictions in the 
Carrefour-Feuilles Platform. [end recording]. 

</TEXT>

