<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "This Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] A group of former Government Ministry soldiers 
occupied the UN offices in Nicaragua for several hours yesterday 
afternoon and evening. Hours after the seizure of the UN 
offices, during which 10 officials were held captive, the former 
soldiers went to the Government Ministry to begin negotiating 
their demands with Deputy Ministers Joaquin Lovo and Frank Cesar 
Reyes. The former soldiers, who arrived with their faces covered 
with red handkerchiefs, were led by Marvin Miranda. They 
demanded prompt compensation for their years of service during 
the former Sandinist regime. 

