<F P=101> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Petrobras Monopoly Said To Increase Oil Imports </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0403135794 Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL in Portuguese 
27 Feb 94 p 1--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PY0403135794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A survey by two energy experts -- professors Adriano 
Pires Rodrigues and Danilo de Souza Dias from Rio de Janeiro 
Federal University -- concluded that if the oil monopoly is 
maintained, our country will become increasingly dependent on 
oil imports. 
  Petrobras is not in a position to make the required 
investments -- $102 billion through the year 2010 -- to maintain 
the current production rate, representing 55 percent of total 
oil consumption. 
  The professors recommend the participation of other 
enterprises in the exploration of new areas and a law to 
regulate this activity. 

</TEXT>

