<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   Congress Approves Emergency Banking Law </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0903025294 Caracas Venezolana de Television Network in 
Spanish 2350 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0903025294 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Venezolana de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From "The News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] An emergency law presented to Congress by Treasury 
Minister Julio Sosa Rodriguez was approved this evening after 
Congress debated it for three hours in a bicameral session. The 
only thing that remains now is for the legislative branch to 
send the document to the executive for confirmation. 
  In a bicameral session, Congress approved a law dealing with 
the nation's financial crisis. MAS [Movement Toward Socialism] 
Deputy Walter Marquez, who has closely followed the Banco Latino 
case, as president of the commission investigating the case, 
gave his opinion on this law: 
  [Begin Marquez recording] The most important points approved 
guarantee bank deposit insurance from 1 to 4 million bolivares 
and the appointment of representatives for the depositors to the 
Intervention Board. Meanwhile, the Intervention Board is 
authorized to pay senior citizens over 60 and people who are in 
a difficult economic situation enough to cover their daily 
expenses. Likewise, the mechanisms to handle financial 
emergencies were established, and in the same manner, mechanisms 
were set up to obtain temporary financial aid. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

