<H3> <TI>   Robaina Continues Visit to Indonesia </TI></H3>
<H4>   Suharto Urges End to Blockade </H4>
<F P=102> FL1103033094 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 0300 GMT 
11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1103033094 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Indonesian Government has condemned the human 
rights campaign against our country and supported the resolution 
to end the U.S. blockade imposed on the island for more than 
three decades. 
  During the meeting with Indonesian President Suharto, Cuban 
Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina, on behalf of Cuban President 
Fidel Castro, conveyed Cuba's appreciation to Indonesia, and 
stressed Cuba's satisfaction over current relations between the 
two countries. 
  Robaina said that our people appreciate the Indonesian food 
assistance, namely the shipment of rice. After a 48-hour visit 
to Indonesia, Robaina left for Laos where he will begin the 
second leg of his tour of India, Cambodia, Malaysia, Vietnam, 
and Myamar, the former Burma. 

</TEXT>

