<H3> <TI>   Robaina Continues Visit to Indonesia </TI></H3>
<H4>   Concludes Visit, Departs for Laos </H4>
<F P=102> FL1003213794 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1003213794 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina departed for 
Laos today on the second leg of his tour of the Asian continent, 
which will include India, Cambodia, Vietnam, and Myanmar, 
formerly known as Burma. 
  Before departing for Laos, Robaina gave Indonesian President 
Suharto a message from his counterpart Fidel Castro, which 
expresses satisfaction with the current state of bilateral 
relations. The text expresses Cuba's desire to continue 
developing ties between the two countries as well as Havana's 
willingness to find new spheres of cooperation. 
  During the meeting, Robaina praised Indonesia and its 
president for their leadership in the Non-Aligned Movement, of 
which Cuba is a member. Suharto stated that Robaina's visit will 
help to strengthen relations between the two countires and 
expand commercial ties. 
  Extensive coverage has been given Robaina's visit to 
Indonesia, one of the most densely populated countries of the 
world, especially by the JAKARTA POST, and the (?regional news). 

</TEXT>

