<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Organization Demands End of U.S. Blockade </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1003213494 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1500 GMT 
10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1003213494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A society of friendship with Cuba was recently 
created in Russia. One of the objectives of this society is to 
seek the lifting of the U.S. blockade against Cuba and the 
development of ties between the Russian and Cuban peoples. 
  In remarks to PRENSA LATINA, (Anatoliy Burlov), vice 
president of the organization, said that the legal registration 
of this society is to promote rapprochement between the two 
nations in important areas such as culture, tourism, and the 
probable creation of joint ventures. (Burlov) said that this new 
society headed by cosmonaut (Vladimir Shatalov) stems from the 
principles of the previous organization founded in 1964 by Yuri 
Gagarin. 
  According to (Shatalov), the main objective of this society 
is to group the true friends of Cuba for the purpose of 
defending bilateral cooperation and the interests of the two 
nations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

