<H3> <TI>   Hispasat Satellite Signal Received in Havana </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1003222294 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1500 GMT 
10 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1003222294 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Pio Luis Machado] </F>
  [Text] For the first time, the Hispasat satellite signal 
has been received in Cuba, on educational television, fulfilling 
one of the agreements of the Ibero-American Summit. This has 
been achieved as the result of the competent, dedicated work of 
the expert satellite and optical-link researchers at the Jose 
Antonio Echeverria Superior Polytechnical School in Havana City. 
  A relevant fact was that at the first interactive conference 
in February, outstanding experts of the Medical Sciences 
Institute received a live satellite signal, enabling them to 
observe three top scientific-level surgeries. 
  During the Hispasat satellite transmissions, a doctor 
observing one of the complex surgeries was able to answer 
questions on the patient's health condition. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

