<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Anti-Aircraft Defense Meeting Held at Western Unit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1003213994 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0100 
GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1003213994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A meeting on anti-aircraft defense was held at unit 
no. 4790 of the Western Army, the best of its kind in Cuba. The 
purpose of the meeting was to analyze the new types of 
preparation for command and control elements under conditions of 
the special period. Furthermore, they analyzed the action to be 
taken by anti-aircraft defense regiments to repel air strikes 
while under a military blockade, and to resist systematic 
demoralization [desgaste sistematico] efforts. The [words 
indistinct] localization and pursuit of enemy targets, and the 
preparation of the reserves and Territorial Troops Militia were 
other issues discussed in this important meeting. Lieutenant 
Colonel Enrique Garces Montesino highlights the reasons this 
unit was selected as the site for the meeting. 
  [Begin Garces recording] During 1991, 1992, and 1993, this 
regiment achieved the distinction of being the best 
anti-aircraft defense regiment because of the results obtained 
in combat training and political preparation, which was 
demonstrated during an inspection carried out by the Ministry of 
the Revolutionary Armed Forces in the western territory in 1993. 
It was rated good, and superior. It was also selected because of 
its achievements in the food program, conservation and 
protection of equipment and armaments, and in improvement of its 
personnel's living conditions. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

