<H3> <TI>   Senator Osny Eugene Charges Accounting Irregularities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1003213294 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1130 
GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1003213294 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Passages within italics in Creole] </F>
  [Excerpt] Senator Osny Eugene says he has discovered 
several irregularities in the files of the Haitian Senate's 
accounting department. Osny Eugene, quaestor of the office 
presided over by Bernard Sansaricq, says he is setting the 
institution in order. 
  [Begin Eugene recording] ...is that all those sections 
were enclosed in a big accounting department. Well, there are a 
number of irregularities that they [not further identified] will 
be unable to discover because the accountant was both the 
person in charge of spending the money and the bursar. 
  I must tell you that a partial audit led us to realize 
that from May to December there were at least four persons -- 
including two who have died and two others who were dismissed -- 
for whom paychecks continued to be written. We are just now 
setting things in order. We do not intend to harm anybody. We do 
not intend to dismiss anybody but we are setting things in 
order, even if it does mean that in the near future we will 
(?have to) convert some employees, by putting them in the right 
place. [passage omitted] [end recording] 

</TEXT>

