<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bishop Ruiz: Peace Accord To Be Signed 14-15 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1103133094 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1103133094 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Good Morning From Mexico" newscast] </F>
  [Text] It is quite probable that the peace dialogue may be 
resumed next week in Chiapas. The situation in the upper part 
of this state is apparently calm. Mario Meneses has a report. 
  [Begin Meneses recording] Everything is calm before the 
holding of the second stage of the peace dialogue. The Chiapas 
residents do not want any more temporary governments and have 
also requested elections this year. In Oaxaca, Bishop Samuel 
Ruiz said a peace agreement will be signed in Chiapas between 
Monday and Tuesday of the coming week. 
  Also, there are so-called civicos that are being given out 
in 
San Cristobal to keep persons from going to church, because 
there is no talk of the world of God, only politics. Some 
groups have threatened to burn the San Cristobal Bishopric 
unless Samuel Ruiz leaves. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

