<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fuel Tank Explodes Near Attorney General's Office </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1003160294 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1526 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1003160294 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Santa Fe de Bogota, 10 Mar (EFE) -- The explosion 
of a domestic fuel tank at a restaurant today injured five 
people and caused alarm in downtown Santa Fe de Bogota, 
according to the capital city's corps of firemen. 
  The explosion broke windows in several buildings and caused 
a 
fire in a six-story building which was promptly extinguished by 
the firemen. The explosion occurred when a fuel supply vehicle 
was filling the restaurant's tanks on Jimenez Avenue. The 
explosion was so strong that early reports asserted that it was 
an attack on the building where the Office of the Attorney 
General is located. 
  According to one employee, all of the windows at the 
Attorney 
General's Office were shattered and there was confusion for 
several minutes. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-10720 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat048_o_94002" </HT>


