<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Future Foreign Minister on Kantor's Upcoming Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1103002794 Santiago EL MERCURIO in Spanish 25 Feb 94 p C2 </F>
<F P=103> PY1103002794 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago EL MERCURIO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Future Chilean Foreign Minister Carlos Figueroa 
on 24 February assessed the visit of U.S. Trade Secretary Mickey 
Kantor for the presidential inauguration as a U.S. Government 
sign that it favors a commercial relationship with Chile. 
  Figueroa commented: "I consider him a very important (U.S.) 
Government official. I also believe his visit is a sign that 
the U.S. Government favors the search for a significant 
commercial relationship with Chile, either through a free trade 
agreement or Chile's acceptance as a NAFTA member, which are, 
precisely, the subjects we are going to discuss here with the 
secretary." 
  Figueroa held a lengthy working meeting at the Diplomatic 
Academy with the outgoing and incoming Foreign Ministry director 
generals. [passage omitted] 
  The meeting's purpose, according to Figueroa, was to review 
all the ministry's tasks, exchange opinions regarding the 
ministry's general guidelines, and to discuss specific subjects. 
  Carlos Figueroa said some of the specific subjects raised 
during the meeting were Chile's bilateral policy and its 
relationship with neighboring countries and the European Union, 
as well as the rapprochement with Mercosur [Common Market of the 
South]. 

</TEXT>

