<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   French Authorize Peruvian Fishing Exports </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1103001494 Madrid EFE in Spanish 0017 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY1103001494 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lima, 9 Mar (EFE) -- The Peruvian Foreign Ministry 
reported that the access of Peruvian fishing products to France 
has returned to normal levels. Today France included Peru on the 
list of countries authorized to export its products to the 
French market. 
  A Foreign Ministry press release reported today that the 
French official newspaper has published information directed to 
French importers of fishing products, incorporating Peru on the 
list of nations authorized to sell them their products. 
  The note adds that the French Government has fulfilled the 
administrative requirement of including Peru on the list of 
countries permitted to export to their market, as it committed 
itself on 24 February when it announced it would do so "as soon 
as possible." 
  On that date, a Peruvian Foreign Ministry note reported that 
French authorities had communicated to the Peruvian Government 
that they were taking the necessary steps to fulfill the 
administrative requirements for publication of the list of 
accepted Peruvian firms. 
  The French Government said on that occasion that "there is 
no 
discrimination" affecting Peruvian fishing products' entry into 
the French market. 
  On 22 February, it was reported in Lima that France had 
forbidden the importation of Peruvian hake as a result of French 
unions' protests demanding protective measures from their 
government. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

