<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Baena Soares Urges Cuban Reinstatement in OAS </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1003213594 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1003213594 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Today, in Santiago de Chile, Joao Baena Soares, 
secretary general of the Organization of American States, called 
for Cuba's reinstatement in the regional organization. Baena 
Soares stated that the nineties are not the sixties. 
  Upon his arrival in Chile, where he will participate in the 
presidential succession ceremony on 11 March, Baena Soares said: 
Many things have changed and it is necessary to consider the 
issue of Cuba's reinsertion into the organization. Baena went on 
to say that he could not predict the decision of OAS members on 
the matter and stated that the subject has not been included in 
the agenda of the general assembly or permanent commission. 

</TEXT>

