<H3> <TI>   `State of Siege' Declared </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1103223994 Guatemala City Teleonce Television in Spanish 
1900 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1103223994 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City Teleonce Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Telepress" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Civil patrolmen of Xalbaquiej Canton, 
Chichicastenango Municipality, El Quiche Department, reportedly 
have declared that locality under a state of siege [as heard], 
the Mutual Support Group, GAM, has announced in a communique 
issued in Guatemala City. 
  The communique states those who are promoting this form of 
extreme measure are participating in a coordinated plan directed 
and organized by military intelligence. According to GAM, this 
coordinated plan, called The Chain [la cadena], encompasses 60 
cantones and covers all the areas of the high plateau. 
  GAM has demanded an immediate explanation from local 
civilian 
and military authorities as to why civilian patrolmen have 
declared a state of siege; it has also urged the ombudsman and 
the attorney general to review the situation. 

</TEXT>

