<H3> <TI>   Police Defuse Several Bombs Around Capital </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1203204794 Panama City ACAN in Spanish 1828 GMT 12 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1203204794 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City ACAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Guatemala, 12 Mar (ACAN-EFE) -- Government sources 
reported today that Guatemalan security forces have defused at 
least four explosive devices in the capital over the last few 
hours. 
  The national Police stated experts found one bomb at the 
telegraph office. 
  Another bomb was found on a bridge near the Olympic village 
in Guatemala City. Police found still another in a private 
office building, and one last device was in a city suburb. 
  Last Sunday, alleged guerrillas blew up a bridge about 20 km 
outside the capital city along the highway toward the Atlantic 
coast. 
  No organization or person has claimed responsibility for 
placing the devices, none of which exploded. 

</TEXT>

