<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Asian Tour Activities Viewed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1103172694 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1502 GMT 
11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1103172694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Having completed the required protocol, Cuban 
Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina and his Lao counterpart 
Somsavat Lengsavat had a friendly talk today on the changing 
international situation. Robaina and his delegation were given a 
warm welcome upon arrival at (Batai) airport in Vientiane. 
Robaina arrived from a visit to Indonesia and Thailand, which 
were the first stops on his tour through Asia. 
  Somsavat Lengsavat described the Cuban delegation's visit as 
a transcendental event that will allow both sides to bring 
themselves up to date on the situations of the two countries and 
explore all possibilities for cooperation in various spheres. 
  According to (Shi Tirak), Lao first deputy minister of 
foreign affairs, Robaina's visit will allow them to strengthen 
bilateral ties in all areas. 
  Tomorrow, Roberto Robaina is scheduled to meet with 
President 
Nouhak Phoumsavan and Prime Minister Khamtai Siphandon. 
Similarly, the Cuban delegation consisting of (Carlos Amores), 
advisor; Teresa Fernandez, deputy director of the Asia and 
Oceania department of the Ministry of Foreign Relations; and 
Cuban Ambassador to Laos Ricardo Danza Sigas will meet with the 
president of the Lao national assembly, (Saban Vinatek). 
  During his stay in Vientiane, Robaina will also meet with 
(Cambo Sonitai), leader of the Cuba-Laos Friendship Association. 
The delegation will continue its Asian tour, and their next stop 
will be Myanmar, formerly known as Burma, after which they will 
travel to Cambodia, India, Malaysia, and Vietnam. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

