<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Views Frei Inauguration </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1103024794 Santiago EL MERCURIO in Spanish 24 Feb 94 p C2 </F>
<F P=103> PY1103024794 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago EL MERCURIO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Various representatives from the Cuban cultural 
field, among them singer Silvio Rodriguez, will attend Chilean 
President-elect Eduardo Frei's inauguration on 11 March. This 
was confirmed by Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina. 
  Robaina said we have not received official invitations for 
the Cuban Government and authorities. He disclosed, however, 
that singer Silvio Rodriguez; the House of the Americas 
director, poet Roberto Fernandez Retamar; and Latin American 
Studies Center Director Luis Suarez have received personal 
invitations to the event. 
  In comments to ANSA, Robaina said: "We hope it (Chile) will 
continue on that path." 
  The foreign minister said Cuba respects the way the Chileans 
have handled the presidential inauguration and reiterated that 
Havana is in no hurry to resume ties with Chile. 
  Chile and Cuba broke diplomatic relations on 11 September 
1973 after the bloody military coup against constitutional 
Chilean President Salvador Allende. 
  The two countries resumed relations at a consular and 
commercial level in 1991, as a prior step to the definite 
normalization of their bilateral relations. 

</TEXT>

