<H3> <TI>   Participant Views `Oil for Cuba' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1403032894 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 0300 GMT 
14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1403032894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Next May, the Mexican organization "For Cuba" [Va 
por Cuba] will send a third shipment that includes over 80 tons 
of lubricating oil, in defiance of the U.S. embargo [embargo] of 
our Caribbean island. The "Oil for Cuba" campaign is in its 
final phase, we already have a figure similar to last year's, 
and the donations continue -- said (Rodolfo Echevarria), 
representative of [words indistinct], who arrived in Havana 
along with over (?250) members of the third Pastors for Peace 
caravan. 
  In a wheelchair because of his progressive neurocerebral 
affliction, Echevarria reported that in the past, the "For Cuba" 
group has sent to the island shipments of lubricants totalling 
175 tons. The organization this time contributed six tons of 
medicines, school supplies, powdered milk, and other articles to 
the Pastors for Peace campaign. 

