<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   PRD Candidate Remarks on Electoral Violence </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1203232394 Panama City Circuito RPC Television in Spanish 
2300 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1203232394 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City Circuito RPC Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Ciro Ortega; from the "RPC Television News" </F>
newscast] 
  [Text] Ernesto Perez Balladares, PRD [Democratic 
Revolutionary Party] presidential candidate, urged other 
political parties to avoid provocations and refrain from 
engaging in electoral violence. 
  Perez Balladares met with members of the Colon Free Zone 
Users Association today. He explained to the businessmen the 
need to reform the law creating the Free Zone, so as to make it 
more functional and to bring it in line with the demands of the 
world's economic market. 
  According to the PRD leader, if he wins the elections he 
will 
appoint the Free Zone manager from a list of nominees proposed 
by those businessmen. Perez Balladares emphasized the need for 
a Panama City-Colon highway, which will become a reality during 
his administration. 
  [Begin recording] [Perez Balladares] There are between 
12,000 
and 14,000 daily vehicle transits on this road. With 
appropriate tolls, this would translate into high revenues that 
could very well pay for the highway, should it be done by 
private enterprise. This is what we want to do. 
  [Unidentified reporter] What do you think of electoral 
violence and how it affects the PRD, given there has been some 
questioning and the Justice and Peace Commission is conducting 
an investigation? 
  [Perez Balladares] I think certain media, not you, have 
blown 
foolish incidents out of proportion. This must not be 
interpreted as a justification, because I do not justify these 
incidents. We are conducting an investigation so we can punish 
those responsible, if anyone is found, but let me tell you 
something: People usually let their emotions go during the 
political season; consequently, we ask our supporters to avoid 
confrontation. Let's not hold our political rallies at the same 
time our political adversaries do. Although they are not our 
enemies, they are still our adversaries. 
  On the other hand, I call on the media to discourage 
violence 
with ill-intended and false reports. I also urge other parties 
to avoid situations we may regret in the future. [end recording] 
  Perez Balladares said he will observe the Justice and Peace 
Commission's decision on a possible sanction over an alleged 
attack by PRD supporters against members of the PDC [Christian 
Democratic Party] and Arnulfist Party. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

